  "texts": [
    "The Fourier transform (FT) 25,26 is a widely-recognized frequency domain decomposition technique in time series analysis.",
    "FT and its modifications can transform an original sequence from time domain to frequency domain, but they ignore trends shifts of time series.",
    "The STL is an important time domain decomposition method, which can effectively decompose a time series data into three distinct subseries.",
    "These three components represent different underlying categories of patterns that exhibit higher predictability.",
    "Wavelet transform (WT) 42,43 and empirical wavelet transformation (EWT) 44,45 are time-frequency domain decomposition methods that are particularly well-suited for the analysis of non-stationary series, as they can provide enhanced local time-frequency information."
  ],
